Angular JS Framework

#AngularJS Expressions
1.AngularJS expressions can be written inside double braces: {{ expression }}.
2.AngularJS expressions can also be written inside a directive: ng-bind="expression".

#AngularJS directives are extended HTML attributes with the prefix ng-.
1.The ng-app directive initializes an AngularJS application.
2.The ng-init directive initializes application data.
3.The ng-model directive binds the value of HTML controls (input, select, textarea) to application data.

#An AngularJS module defines an application.
1.The module is a container for the different parts of an application.
2.The module is a container for the application controllers.
3.Controllers always belong to a module.

#Data binding in AngularJS is the synchronization between the model and the view.

#AngularJS Controllers
1.AngularJS applications are controlled by controllers.
2.The ng-controller directive defines the application controller.
3.A controller is a JavaScript Object, created by a standard JavaScript object constructor.



#AngularJS Services
1.A service is a function, or object, that is available for, and limited to, your AngularJS application.
2.AngularJS has about 30 built-in services. One of them is the $location service.

#AngularJS AJAX
$http is an AngularJS service for reading data from remote servers.
